WEBVTT

00:00:06.010 --> 00:00:09.070
She made her way in here,
and as you can see…

00:00:09.070 --> 00:00:10.680
Jeez…

00:00:10.680 --> 00:00:12.780
It's unfortunate how the
Japan Cup turned out.

00:00:12.820 --> 00:00:14.820
{\an7}Tokyo - #5 Day 8 - 11th Race
Japan Cup (G1)
1st #11 El Condor Pasa
Team: Rigil
Country: Japan
2nd #1 Air Groove
Team: Rigil
Country: Japan
3rd #9 Special Week
Team: Spica
Country: Japan

00:00:16.610 --> 00:00:19.120
I think she must
have been really sad.

00:00:19.120 --> 00:00:23.620
I'm sure she wanted to win because she
was supposed to run in it with you.

00:00:23.620 --> 00:00:26.070
I hope Spe-chan is okay.

00:00:26.070 --> 00:00:28.040
She's been here every day since then.

00:00:28.040 --> 00:00:30.590
Suzuka-san, how are you feeling?!

00:00:30.590 --> 00:00:32.010
Are you hungry?

00:00:32.010 --> 00:00:33.340
Are you thirsty?

00:00:33.340 --> 00:00:34.340
I'll get you some tea.

00:00:34.770 --> 00:00:35.680
That's hot!

00:00:36.570 --> 00:00:40.070
I'm happy she's trying to cheer me up, but…

00:00:40.070 --> 00:00:42.640
I hope she's been training.

00:00:42.640 --> 00:00:45.640
Yeah, though she isn't
really getting anywhere.

00:00:45.640 --> 00:00:47.650
{\an7}Let's run together! — Special Week
See you on the tracks again! —El Condor Pasa
Free food when you get back! On the trainer. —Gold Ship

00:00:47.650 --> 00:00:49.150
{\an8}Let's run together!
Special Week

00:00:48.330 --> 00:00:51.340
I can't wait to run again.

00:00:51.950 --> 00:00:53.740
I want to start training again.

00:00:53.740 --> 00:00:56.260
I told you that you can't
rush into these things.

00:00:56.260 --> 00:00:57.110
Yes…

00:00:57.580 --> 00:00:58.760
But on the off chance…

00:00:58.760 --> 00:00:59.870
You'll be able to run again!

00:00:59.870 --> 00:01:03.290
You're going to run with
me once you get better!

00:01:03.290 --> 00:01:04.370
You were awake?

00:01:04.370 --> 00:01:06.960
I'll do anything for you, Suzuka!

00:01:06.960 --> 00:01:10.250
First, we need to talk about what
you did wrong at the Japan Cup.

00:01:10.250 --> 00:01:12.000
Suzuka-san, I'll see you again tomorrow!

00:01:21.730 --> 00:01:26.950
Do you hear the fanfare as
we race towards the finish?

00:01:26.950 --> 00:01:33.480
I want to see that shining future with you

00:01:35.530 --> 00:01:41.830
{\an8}Umamusume

00:01:37.400 --> 00:01:41.700
{\an8}Pretty Derby

00:01:43.710 --> 00:01:49.430
If we just start to run, that's
where our story will begin

00:01:49.430 --> 00:01:54.450
It's always waiting right in front of us

00:01:54.450 --> 00:02:00.060
If you reach out just a little
more, we can seize that glory

00:02:00.060 --> 00:02:06.920
Aim for the top, challenge
them all, and it's off to the races

00:02:07.730 --> 00:02:12.920
Even the goddess of victory will be dazzled

00:02:12.920 --> 00:02:20.200
By your big debut that's just around the bend

00:02:20.200 --> 00:02:25.620
So can you hear the fanfare
as we race towards the finish?

00:02:25.620 --> 00:02:31.090
I want to see that shining future with you

00:02:31.090 --> 00:02:36.600
Let's overtake them all! It's
a track laid out just for you!

00:02:36.600 --> 00:02:44.360
Your dreams are at the finish if you believe

00:02:46.020 --> 00:02:50.020
{\an8}Race 8

00:02:46.020 --> 00:02:50.020
{\an8}For You

00:02:50.020 --> 00:02:52.020
Happy New Year!

00:02:50.020 --> 00:02:52.020
{\an9}It's almost time for the
Winter
Dream
Trophy

00:02:52.020 --> 00:02:56.110
It's now the morning of the WDT,
the Winter Dream Trophy.

00:02:56.110 --> 00:03:03.450
{\an8}Early-Spring Special New Racer!!
WDT Special!!

00:02:56.110 --> 00:03:00.740
{\an4}Analysis:
Hosoe Junko

00:02:56.110 --> 00:03:00.740
{\an6}Host:
Akasaka Misato

00:02:56.470 --> 00:02:58.430
<i>I can't wait to see what happens.</i>

00:02:58.430 --> 00:03:00.470
<i>The Dream Trophy comes twice a year.</i>

00:03:00.470 --> 00:03:01.780
<i>It's a contest where star horse girls</i>

00:03:01.780 --> 00:03:03.450
<i>who have earned the right
to perform can compete.</i>

00:03:03.450 --> 00:03:06.410
<i>It's amazing just to be able to be out there.</i>

00:03:06.410 --> 00:03:09.960
<i>It's a real dream roster this year!</i>

00:03:10.370 --> 00:03:12.580
<i>The race will start this evening.</i>

00:03:13.180 --> 00:03:16.620
<i>We have a video promoting all the
horse girls that'll be in the race.</i>

00:03:16.620 --> 00:03:17.960
<i>Please take a look!</i>

00:03:18.910 --> 00:03:20.420
<i>Victory…</i>

00:03:23.700 --> 00:03:25.680
Suzuka-san, I'm here to get you.

00:03:29.160 --> 00:03:31.020
{\an4}Permission Slip
Silence Suzuka

00:03:29.300 --> 00:03:31.020
I'm excited, too.

00:03:31.020 --> 00:03:32.770
Looks like you're all ready.

00:03:32.770 --> 00:03:33.850
Let's go!

00:03:33.850 --> 00:03:36.400
{\an8}Kotakeya

00:03:36.030 --> 00:03:37.460
There she is!

00:03:37.460 --> 00:03:38.950
Hey!

00:03:40.370 --> 00:03:41.510
Sorry for taking so long.

00:03:43.710 --> 00:03:44.810
Ta-dah!

00:03:44.060 --> 00:03:44.820
Hey!

00:03:44.820 --> 00:03:46.740
Her cast is off!

00:03:47.170 --> 00:03:48.830
So you can run now?

00:03:48.830 --> 00:03:50.670
Of course not.

00:03:50.670 --> 00:03:52.040
Hey!

00:03:52.420 --> 00:03:54.570
You'll have to go into rehab now, huh?

00:03:54.570 --> 00:03:56.340
I hope you do well.

00:03:57.170 --> 00:03:58.140
Thank you.

00:03:58.140 --> 00:04:00.550
Let's eat something really good today.

00:04:00.550 --> 00:04:02.740
Our trainer will pay.

00:04:02.740 --> 00:04:03.510
All right!

00:04:03.510 --> 00:04:06.220
I'll handle the New Year's party.

00:04:22.140 --> 00:04:25.340
Happy New Year!

00:04:25.930 --> 00:04:28.570
Why do I have to get everything ready?

00:04:28.570 --> 00:04:30.770
You said you'd handle the
New Year's party, didn't you?

00:04:30.770 --> 00:04:32.550
You look good in that apron.

00:04:32.550 --> 00:04:34.820
In the Mejiro household,
my servants handle work like this.

00:04:34.820 --> 00:04:39.380
I guess I shouldn't expect you guys
to be able to handle any housework.

00:04:39.420 --> 00:04:41.380
Ow!

00:04:41.380 --> 00:04:43.890
Suzuka-san, it doesn't hurt, does it?

00:04:43.890 --> 00:04:45.510
No, I'm fine.

00:04:45.510 --> 00:04:48.350
Here's your Trainer Special Hot Pot!

00:04:49.650 --> 00:04:51.560
Let's dig in.

00:04:51.560 --> 00:04:53.140
You're going to gain weight again.

00:04:53.140 --> 00:04:56.600
What do you mean, "again"?!

00:04:56.600 --> 00:04:58.660
I'll give you some of mine.

00:04:58.660 --> 00:05:00.580
Oh, thank you.

00:05:01.540 --> 00:05:03.240
The WDT is going to start!

00:05:03.740 --> 00:05:06.420
<i>All the fans for all the horse girls,</i>

00:05:05.470 --> 00:05:08.990
{\an8}Winter Dream Trophy

00:05:06.420 --> 00:05:10.990
<i>and all their dreams: it's time
to start the Winter Dream Trophy.</i>

00:05:07.410 --> 00:05:08.990
{\an8}Tokyo - Turf - 2400m

00:05:10.990 --> 00:05:13.370
<i>Will the Emperor, Symboli Rudolf, win?</i>

00:05:13.370 --> 00:05:15.910
<i>Or will it be the
Shadow Roll Monster, Narita Brian?</i>

00:05:15.910 --> 00:05:17.830
<i>The Super Car, Maruzensky?</i>

00:05:17.830 --> 00:05:19.880
<i>The Two-Stage Rocket, Fuji Kiseki?</i>

00:05:19.880 --> 00:05:22.460
<i>Or the Monster from Afar, Oguri Cap?!</i>

00:05:26.490 --> 00:05:29.220
<i>They're all out of the gates!</i>

00:05:30.470 --> 00:05:33.470
Prez, you can do it!

00:05:44.440 --> 00:05:47.070
The president is so cool.

00:05:47.070 --> 00:05:49.610
I want us to run there someday, too!

00:05:49.610 --> 00:05:51.490
That's a good goal.

00:05:51.490 --> 00:05:54.930
Then we're going to need
to work especially hard.

00:05:54.930 --> 00:05:55.440
Yeah.

00:05:55.440 --> 00:05:56.490
That's right.

00:05:55.870 --> 00:06:01.380
{\an7}G-I
G-II
G-III
Open Special
Ranked Class / Junior Class
First Debut • Unranked

00:05:56.490 --> 00:05:59.220
If you win a lot in the Twinkle Series,

00:05:59.220 --> 00:06:01.380
you'll be able to get into the Dream Trophy.

00:06:01.380 --> 00:06:03.630
I-I want to run in it, too!

00:06:03.630 --> 00:06:06.590
I want to run with the
president and Suzuka-san.

00:06:06.590 --> 00:06:10.060
Spe, you're fast when you're in the zone,

00:06:10.060 --> 00:06:11.780
but you're too inconsistent.

00:06:11.780 --> 00:06:14.140
It's going to take more than the
Derby to make you the best in Japan.

00:06:14.140 --> 00:06:14.770
Right!

00:06:15.210 --> 00:06:16.690
Vodka, Scarlet,

00:06:16.690 --> 00:06:20.970
it's true you'll get faster much quicker
if you have a rival on your team,

00:06:20.970 --> 00:06:22.890
but you gotta make sure you
keep up with each other.

00:06:22.890 --> 00:06:23.610
Right!

00:06:23.610 --> 00:06:27.580
Teio, everyone knows that you're talented,

00:06:27.580 --> 00:06:28.940
but that's not good enough on its own.

00:06:28.940 --> 00:06:31.170
You need to surpass that.

00:06:31.170 --> 00:06:32.180
Right.

00:06:32.180 --> 00:06:35.850
McQueen, you're a daughter
of the famous Mejiro family.

00:06:35.850 --> 00:06:37.650
If you want people to respect
that name, work hard,

00:06:37.650 --> 00:06:39.310
no matter how dirty you have to get.

00:06:39.310 --> 00:06:41.130
I know that.

00:06:41.130 --> 00:06:42.450
GolShi…

00:06:43.390 --> 00:06:45.300
Uh… well, just run however you want.

00:06:45.300 --> 00:06:46.180
Got it.

00:06:46.180 --> 00:06:48.150
And you, Suzuka…

00:06:48.150 --> 00:06:48.800
Yes.

00:06:48.800 --> 00:06:51.710
Last year, you helped me
realize some of my dreams,

00:06:52.140 --> 00:06:53.840
but it's not enough.

00:06:53.840 --> 00:06:55.560
I want to dream more with you.

00:06:55.960 --> 00:06:57.700
Work hard on your rehab.

00:06:57.700 --> 00:06:58.600
Right!

00:06:58.600 --> 00:07:01.090
Spica is going to beat Rigil this year!

00:07:01.090 --> 00:07:02.790
We're going to work harder than them!

00:07:02.790 --> 00:07:04.060
Right!

00:07:04.060 --> 00:07:05.490
Anyway, let's go.

00:07:05.490 --> 00:07:07.070
Go where?

00:07:14.410 --> 00:07:16.160
{\an8}Bad Luck

00:07:19.080 --> 00:07:20.850
{\an8}Charm

00:07:25.040 --> 00:07:27.560
You're Silence Suzuka-san, aren't you?

00:07:27.560 --> 00:07:28.910
Y-Yeah.

00:07:28.910 --> 00:07:31.320
Please shake my hand!

00:07:31.320 --> 00:07:32.890
Is your leg okay?

00:07:32.890 --> 00:07:33.490
Yes.

00:07:33.490 --> 00:07:35.140
We're waiting for you to come back.

00:07:35.140 --> 00:07:37.730
<i>Everyone's waiting for
Suzuka-san to come back.</i>

00:07:37.730 --> 00:07:39.560
Oh, it's Special Week!

00:07:39.560 --> 00:07:40.560
Y-Yeah.

00:07:40.560 --> 00:07:43.470
Too bad you didn't win the Japan Cup.

00:07:43.470 --> 00:07:44.770
Y-Yeah…

00:07:44.770 --> 00:07:46.620
{\an8}Keep working hard out there.

00:07:45.640 --> 00:07:47.770
Everyone, let's go!

00:07:51.490 --> 00:07:53.940
I pray that Suzuka heals up.

00:07:53.940 --> 00:07:57.220
{\an8}Also, that orange juice starts
coming out of faucets.

00:07:56.260 --> 00:07:58.850
<i>I'm going to make Spica into the best team.</i>

00:07:58.850 --> 00:08:00.620
<i>I'm not losing to her!</i>

00:08:00.620 --> 00:08:02.360
<i>I'm going to catch up to the president!</i>

00:08:02.360 --> 00:08:04.780
<i>I'm going to make the Mejiro
name proud with my running.</i>

00:08:04.780 --> 00:08:07.080
<i>I pray that I'll be able to run with Suzuka!</i>

00:08:07.690 --> 00:08:10.950
<i>I'm going to recover and race again.</i>

00:08:14.180 --> 00:08:16.050
<i>Hello, Mom.</i>

00:08:16.050 --> 00:08:19.810
<i>I've been accompanying
Suzuka-san to rehab every day.</i>

00:08:27.370 --> 00:08:28.940
<i>I see how hard she's working,</i>

00:08:28.940 --> 00:08:31.250
<i>and I can't help but be
reminded how great she is.</i>

00:08:40.490 --> 00:08:42.620
<i>Everyone on the team is winning a lot.</i>

00:08:42.620 --> 00:08:44.890
<i>I guess our prayers from the start
of this year are being answered.</i>

00:08:50.610 --> 00:08:52.260
<i>It'll be summer soon,</i>

00:08:52.260 --> 00:08:54.470
<i>and Suzuka-san's leg should
be fully healed soon.</i>

00:08:55.930 --> 00:08:57.820
<i>I can't wait.</i>

00:08:59.930 --> 00:09:03.930
{\an4}Umamusume

00:08:59.930 --> 00:09:03.930
{\an4}Pretty Derby

00:09:07.900 --> 00:09:10.490
Suzuka-san, take it easy at first.

00:09:10.490 --> 00:09:11.610
Easy, okay?

00:09:11.610 --> 00:09:13.440
I'll be fine with one lap.

00:09:13.440 --> 00:09:15.070
Don't overdo it
just because it's fun.

00:09:15.070 --> 00:09:16.140
Right.

00:09:16.140 --> 00:09:18.470
All right, let's go.

00:09:18.470 --> 00:09:24.330
One, two…

00:09:24.330 --> 00:09:39.510
{\an8}One, two…

00:09:25.620 --> 00:09:28.610
I wonder how many months it's been
since we've gotten to run with Suzuka-san.

00:09:28.610 --> 00:09:29.420
Yeah…

00:09:29.420 --> 00:09:31.090
Nine months and three days.

00:09:31.460 --> 00:09:32.800
You counted, huh?

00:09:32.800 --> 00:09:35.670
You'll be putting more strain
on your leg, so be careful.

00:09:35.670 --> 00:09:36.680
I know.

00:09:36.680 --> 00:09:38.330
Spe, you're being annoying.

00:09:38.330 --> 00:09:39.510
S-Sorry!

00:09:45.150 --> 00:09:47.980
Oh, is that Suzuka?

00:09:50.690 --> 00:09:54.420
Suzuka, you can run now?

00:09:54.420 --> 00:09:56.020
Air Groove-senpai…

00:09:56.020 --> 00:09:58.050
When will you make it back on the track?

00:09:58.050 --> 00:10:01.240
I don't know yet, but I definitely will.

00:10:01.240 --> 00:10:04.320
I see. Come back soon.

00:10:04.320 --> 00:10:07.620
And let's have another good
race like the Takarazuka Kinen.

00:10:07.620 --> 00:10:08.640
Yeah.

00:10:08.640 --> 00:10:11.000
Air Groove, let's go.

00:10:11.000 --> 00:10:13.100
Sorry, I couldn't help it.

00:10:13.100 --> 00:10:15.660
Suzuka, I'm glad to see you here.

00:10:15.660 --> 00:10:17.290
I can't wait for you to get back out there.

00:10:17.290 --> 00:10:19.960
I really feel that way
as your former teammate.

00:10:19.960 --> 00:10:20.720
Right.

00:10:20.720 --> 00:10:23.210
Special Week, sorry for bothering you.

00:10:23.210 --> 00:10:25.290
No, I'm happy.

00:10:25.290 --> 00:10:26.220
Happy?

00:10:26.220 --> 00:10:29.250
Everyone's waiting for
Suzuka-san to come back.

00:10:29.250 --> 00:10:31.660
Suzuka-san is amazing!

00:10:31.660 --> 00:10:32.690
That's not…

00:10:32.690 --> 00:10:35.720
Oh yeah, you're going to be in
the Takarazuka this year, right?

00:10:35.720 --> 00:10:36.780
Yes.

00:10:36.780 --> 00:10:38.740
Grass Wonder's running for Rigil.

00:10:38.740 --> 00:10:39.900
I know.

00:10:39.900 --> 00:10:42.150
It'll be my first time running with her.

00:10:42.150 --> 00:10:43.950
Let's make it a good race.

00:10:44.370 --> 00:10:45.190
Right!

00:10:55.510 --> 00:10:57.430
Grass Wonder, do you have a moment?

00:10:58.050 --> 00:10:59.420
What is it?

00:11:00.050 --> 00:11:04.430
You know that Special Week will be running
the Takarazuka Kinen for Spica, right?

00:11:04.430 --> 00:11:04.930
Yes.

00:11:05.340 --> 00:11:08.800
She's becoming quite the
star among your generation,

00:11:08.800 --> 00:11:10.730
but the same could also be
said of you, Grass Wonder.

00:11:11.110 --> 00:11:12.840
Thank you very much,

00:11:12.840 --> 00:11:16.390
but beating Spe-chan will be tough.

00:11:16.390 --> 00:11:19.260
I guess winning the Arima Kinen
didn't go to your head.

00:11:19.260 --> 00:11:20.740
It's made me desperate to work harder.

00:11:20.990 --> 00:11:22.780
That's the spirit.

00:11:23.370 --> 00:11:26.770
Whatever you do, work at
it with all your heart.

00:11:26.770 --> 00:11:28.300
Do your best.

00:11:28.300 --> 00:11:30.290
Keep those feelings with you.

00:11:30.940 --> 00:11:32.740
I'll do my best.

00:11:36.040 --> 00:11:38.400
{\an8}Rehab Exercises You Can Do at Home

00:11:40.940 --> 00:11:42.260
Hmm?

00:11:42.530 --> 00:11:44.720
{\an8}Carrot Books

00:11:52.220 --> 00:11:56.270
I have to go help Suzuka-san, so I won't
be able to eat lunch with you for a while.

00:11:56.270 --> 00:11:57.470
I'm sorry!

00:11:58.400 --> 00:12:00.220
Spe-chan, I'm back!

00:12:00.220 --> 00:12:01.720
Welcome back, Urara-chan!

00:12:01.720 --> 00:12:02.740
Huh?

00:12:16.630 --> 00:12:17.660
What's the matter?

00:12:17.660 --> 00:12:19.220
You're spacing out.

00:12:19.710 --> 00:12:24.500
Well, Spe-chan has been a bit odd lately.

00:12:24.500 --> 00:12:25.940
It doesn't matter who you're up against.

00:12:25.940 --> 00:12:27.930
At Rigil, we always do our best.

00:12:27.930 --> 00:12:30.070
Don't think about anything you don't have to.

00:12:30.650 --> 00:12:31.930
Right.

00:12:34.780 --> 00:12:35.810
That's cold.

00:12:35.810 --> 00:12:38.130
I'm going to tape it up.

00:12:38.130 --> 00:12:39.320
Thank you.

00:12:40.330 --> 00:12:43.410
I still can't move my legs
and arms the way I want,

00:12:44.230 --> 00:12:45.820
but I had fun.

00:12:46.310 --> 00:12:48.780
It makes me happy to run.

00:12:50.170 --> 00:12:51.770
Me, too!

00:12:51.770 --> 00:12:54.750
Let's build up more muscles,
so we can run faster!

00:12:55.820 --> 00:12:56.850
Yeah.

00:13:48.260 --> 00:13:50.930
Suzuka-san, are you okay?!

00:13:50.930 --> 00:13:52.110
Spe-chan…

00:13:52.110 --> 00:13:54.650
Are you in pain?

00:13:54.650 --> 00:13:56.090
I'm okay.

00:13:56.090 --> 00:13:58.130
Focus on yourself for now.

00:13:58.130 --> 00:13:59.170
But…

00:13:59.170 --> 00:14:01.450
You have the Takarazuka Kinen
this weekend, right?

00:14:02.130 --> 00:14:02.860
Yeah.

00:14:02.860 --> 00:14:05.590
I want you to win, Spe-chan.

00:14:06.490 --> 00:14:08.200
Hey, Spe!

00:14:08.200 --> 00:14:10.700
Don't slack off!

00:14:09.020 --> 00:14:10.700
I'm sorry!

00:14:11.040 --> 00:14:15.940
Jeez, I told you not to work yourself up.

00:14:15.940 --> 00:14:16.870
Yeah…

00:14:21.340 --> 00:14:22.920
Oh, Grass-chan.

00:14:22.920 --> 00:14:26.210
Um, do you want to get lunch, Spe-chan?

00:14:26.210 --> 00:14:28.090
I have to do something with Suzuka-san—

00:14:29.570 --> 00:14:31.660
Then I'll go with you.

00:14:35.220 --> 00:14:37.570
Is it okay for me to be here?

00:14:37.570 --> 00:14:39.410
Of course it is.

00:14:39.410 --> 00:14:42.010
I can't just hog you all to myself.

00:14:42.010 --> 00:14:45.070
It's been a long time since we've
had lunch with you, Spe-chan.

00:14:45.070 --> 00:14:46.490
Oh, right.

00:14:46.490 --> 00:14:48.520
I got a letter from El.

00:14:48.520 --> 00:14:49.320
El-chan?!

00:14:50.370 --> 00:14:51.320
Let's see…

00:14:51.320 --> 00:14:53.530
"Bonjour, it's El."

00:14:53.530 --> 00:14:54.950
"Are you all doing well?"

00:14:55.510 --> 00:15:00.130
<i>I thought I was going to win hands down,
but I came in second in the Prix d'Ispahan.</i>

00:15:00.130 --> 00:15:04.050
<i>But I'm totally going to win the
next Grand Prix de Saint-Cloud!</i>

00:15:04.050 --> 00:15:05.260
<i>Cheer me on!</i>

00:15:05.260 --> 00:15:06.260
<i>Salut!</i>

00:15:07.250 --> 00:15:09.370
She hasn't changed, even overseas.

00:15:10.900 --> 00:15:13.970
I'm thinking of going to America.

00:15:13.970 --> 00:15:17.590
Suzuka-san, I'm running in the
Takarazuka Kinen this Sunday,

00:15:17.590 --> 00:15:19.490
so I'll be gone for a little bit.

00:15:19.490 --> 00:15:21.660
I won't be able to help you out,

00:15:21.660 --> 00:15:23.820
but I'll be right back after it's over.

00:15:23.820 --> 00:15:25.780
Let's train together.

00:15:25.780 --> 00:15:26.830
Yes.

00:15:26.830 --> 00:15:30.450
Suzuka-san, how is your leg?

00:15:30.450 --> 00:15:32.430
It doesn't hurt anymore.

00:15:32.430 --> 00:15:34.710
I want to get back to racing
as quickly as I can.

00:15:34.710 --> 00:15:38.470
I was anxious throughout
my rehabilitation, too.

00:15:38.470 --> 00:15:40.460
Oh, yeah, the same thing
happened to you.

00:15:40.460 --> 00:15:45.720
Yes, that's why I was so upset
during the Mainichi Okan.

00:15:45.720 --> 00:15:48.330
I couldn't reach my full speed.

00:15:49.380 --> 00:15:52.010
That was before Suzuka got hurt.

00:15:52.010 --> 00:15:54.020
Sorry for bringing that up.

00:15:54.020 --> 00:15:57.180
Anyway, you shouldn't rush yourself.

00:15:57.180 --> 00:15:59.130
Grass-chan, thank you.

00:15:59.130 --> 00:16:00.810
I won't rush. I'll take it day by day.

00:16:01.410 --> 00:16:03.950
Suzuka-san, I'll help you, too!

00:16:03.950 --> 00:16:04.980
Yeah.

00:16:04.980 --> 00:16:05.950
Um…

00:16:06.950 --> 00:16:11.030
Spe-chan, you're thinking about
the Takarazuka Kinen, right?

00:16:11.030 --> 00:16:11.820
Yeah!

00:16:12.420 --> 00:16:14.200
I'm glad, then.

00:16:14.200 --> 00:16:18.700
I want to be as cool as
Suzuka-san was last year!

00:16:19.070 --> 00:16:20.540
What about me?

00:16:20.540 --> 00:16:21.390
Huh?

00:16:21.390 --> 00:16:23.210
Never mind. It's nothing.

00:16:23.930 --> 00:16:25.580
Let's do our best.

00:16:25.580 --> 00:16:27.030
That was good.

00:16:29.670 --> 00:16:31.550
I'll get it!

00:16:31.550 --> 00:16:33.380
Hey, wait.

00:16:34.050 --> 00:16:37.510
Those two are really close.

00:16:37.510 --> 00:16:39.470
They are…

00:16:41.070 --> 00:16:44.230
<i>It's time for the match all fans of
the Twinkle Series are waiting for:</i>

00:16:44.230 --> 00:16:46.560
<i>the Takarazuka Kinen.</i>

00:16:46.560 --> 00:16:49.600
Hosoe-san, who do you think
we should keep an eye on?

00:16:49.600 --> 00:16:52.760
I'm sure it'll be a close match between
Grass Wonder and Special Week.

00:16:52.760 --> 00:16:55.570
They both have what it takes,
and they're both popular.

00:16:56.170 --> 00:16:59.830
<i>You can feel the passion here,
with Grass Wonder joining us.</i>

00:16:59.830 --> 00:17:01.360
<i>It'll be interesting.</i>

00:17:01.360 --> 00:17:06.290
{\an8}Silence Suzuka's performance from last
year really left an impression on us.

00:17:04.500 --> 00:17:05.660
All right.

00:17:07.340 --> 00:17:11.110
<i>Spe-chan, we'll finally get to run together.</i>

00:17:11.800 --> 00:17:14.350
<i>I want a hard fight.</i>

00:17:15.300 --> 00:17:18.740
She looks more serious
than she ever has before.

00:17:18.740 --> 00:17:19.750
Let me see.

00:17:19.750 --> 00:17:20.610
Sure.

00:17:28.770 --> 00:17:31.190
Spe, focus! Focus!

00:17:31.190 --> 00:17:34.190
<i>All the horse girls have entered their gates.</i>

00:17:34.190 --> 00:17:35.530
<i>Suzuka-san…</i>

00:17:35.530 --> 00:17:37.190
<i>The Takarazuka Kinen…</i>

00:17:38.660 --> 00:17:40.220
<i>…has started!</i>

00:17:40.220 --> 00:17:43.650
<i>Special Week and Grass Wonder
are about to go at it.</i>

00:17:43.650 --> 00:17:47.070
<i>It'll be important to see who makes their
move toward the second half of the race.</i>

00:17:47.710 --> 00:17:49.830
They've passed the second turn.

00:17:49.830 --> 00:17:51.700
<i>Nisha Mother Great is in the lead!</i>

00:17:51.700 --> 00:17:53.560
<i>The other eleven horse
girls are following her.</i>

00:17:53.560 --> 00:17:55.460
<i>King Halo is in second, no, third.</i>

00:17:55.460 --> 00:17:57.700
<i>Kin'iryoutei is trying to
come up from the inside.</i>

00:17:57.700 --> 00:17:59.810
<i>Special Week is following in fifth.</i>

00:17:59.810 --> 00:18:01.350
<i>Grass Wonder is right behind her.</i>

00:18:02.170 --> 00:18:03.350
<i>Suzuka-san!</i>

00:18:03.350 --> 00:18:06.330
<i>Grass Wonder is sticking with Special Week.</i>

00:18:06.330 --> 00:18:08.790
<i>Grass Wonder is strong
when she gets like this.</i>

00:18:09.510 --> 00:18:10.860
Spe-chan…

00:18:11.790 --> 00:18:13.860
<i>Suzuka-san, are you watching?</i>

00:18:13.860 --> 00:18:17.700
<i>I'm running the same race you did!</i>

00:18:18.860 --> 00:18:22.290
<i>Special Week is looking around!</i>

00:18:22.290 --> 00:18:24.660
<i>Grass Wonder is behind you!</i>

00:18:25.810 --> 00:18:29.670
<i>Spe-chan, you're up against me today.</i>

00:18:32.000 --> 00:18:34.420
<i>They've made the third turn,
and are now entering the fourth.</i>

00:18:34.420 --> 00:18:36.370
<i>If I was Suzuka-san…</i>

00:18:36.950 --> 00:18:39.930
Special Week has made her move!

00:18:39.930 --> 00:18:41.710
We can't!

00:18:41.010 --> 00:18:42.430
{\an8}Special Week has taken the lead!

00:18:42.430 --> 00:18:44.430
<i>The crowd is going wild!</i>

00:18:44.430 --> 00:18:46.410
<i>Will she be able to keep
her lead until the end?!</i>

00:18:49.560 --> 00:18:52.060
<i>Grass Wonder is coming up from the outside!</i>

00:18:52.060 --> 00:18:55.220
<i>They've finished the fourth turn,
and they're in the last stretch!</i>

00:18:55.220 --> 00:18:58.320
<i>Grass Wonder and Special Week
are going to fight it out!</i>

00:19:05.660 --> 00:19:11.330
<i>Spe-chan isn't going to
give me a real fight today.</i>

00:19:12.750 --> 00:19:15.180
<i>Grass Wonder's in the lead now!</i>

00:19:15.180 --> 00:19:18.910
<i>Grass Wonder just blew past Special Week!</i>

00:19:21.370 --> 00:19:22.300
<i>No way…</i>

00:19:22.830 --> 00:19:26.010
<i>Suzuka-san's watching!</i>

00:19:27.210 --> 00:19:29.770
<i>Grass Wonder! Grass Wonder is in the lead!</i>

00:19:29.770 --> 00:19:32.780
<i>Grass Wonder had it in her!</i>

00:19:32.780 --> 00:19:33.690
She just

00:19:33.690 --> 00:19:35.450
<i>took first!</i>

00:19:35.450 --> 00:19:38.530
<i>Special Week came in second,
three horse lengths behind!</i>

00:19:56.970 --> 00:19:59.970
I was able to give it my all
because I was up against you.

00:20:01.420 --> 00:20:05.010
Did you give it your all against me?

00:20:46.700 --> 00:20:48.100
Trainer-san…

00:20:48.810 --> 00:20:51.110
I thought you'd be here.

00:20:51.620 --> 00:20:53.190
I'm sorry.

00:20:53.190 --> 00:20:54.840
Racing isn't easy.

00:20:54.840 --> 00:20:58.090
Your mental state is important during a race.

00:20:58.820 --> 00:20:59.750
Yes…

00:20:59.750 --> 00:21:03.110
Spe, what were you thinking about
when you were racing today?

00:21:03.950 --> 00:21:05.860
<i>Suzuka-san, are you watching?</i>

00:21:06.300 --> 00:21:08.340
<i>I'm running the same race you did!</i>

00:21:08.340 --> 00:21:09.950
<i>If I was Suzuka-san…</i>

00:21:10.690 --> 00:21:12.460
I was thinking about Suzuka-san.

00:21:12.460 --> 00:21:13.890
Who are you?

00:21:13.890 --> 00:21:15.450
Special Week.

00:21:15.450 --> 00:21:18.160
And who were you up against today?

00:21:18.160 --> 00:21:19.960
Grass-chan.

00:21:19.960 --> 00:21:21.450
Hey, Spe.

00:21:21.450 --> 00:21:23.460
What's your goal?

00:21:23.890 --> 00:21:26.630
I'm going to run with Suzuka-san.

00:21:26.630 --> 00:21:28.100
Was that it?

00:21:28.100 --> 00:21:29.010
Huh?

00:21:33.270 --> 00:21:37.020
I wanted my mom to watch me win.

00:21:37.990 --> 00:21:40.050
I promised my mom…

00:21:42.140 --> 00:21:44.880
I said I'd be the best horse girl in Japan.

00:21:44.880 --> 00:21:46.030
That's right.

00:21:46.030 --> 00:21:49.230
You're going to be the best
horse girl in Japan, right?

00:21:49.230 --> 00:21:51.200
You don't have time to pay
attention to other things.

00:21:51.200 --> 00:21:53.810
That's right.

00:21:53.810 --> 00:21:55.120
This fall…

00:21:55.120 --> 00:21:57.120
You're winning all of your races.

00:21:59.420 --> 00:22:00.410
Fall…

00:22:05.470 --> 00:22:06.720
{\an8}Charm

00:22:25.650 --> 00:22:28.810
In a dash, in a flash,
just a little more now,

00:22:28.720 --> 00:22:31.550
each new race like a dream neverending

00:22:31.430 --> 00:22:34.360
Every one of us will blaze a
trail aimed right for the stars

00:22:34.240 --> 00:22:39.410
Together we'll run! Let's
go! Our starting gate!

00:22:48.540 --> 00:22:53.990
With curiosity in hand, go tug
on tomorrow's tail and say hello

00:22:53.870 --> 00:22:58.870
It's right there, so go on and close
the gap now (Right here and now!)

00:22:59.580 --> 00:23:05.060
Can't play by the rules they tell
you! Gotta learn it all by experience!

00:23:04.960 --> 00:23:09.900
If we just plan to run for the
end, everything will turn out okay!

00:23:10.060 --> 00:23:13.930
Can't get me down,
hesitate, or go too slowly!

00:23:15.680 --> 00:23:19.650
We know that deep in our hearts is a song

00:23:19.730 --> 00:23:22.870
that sings "give it your all"! Make it shine!

00:23:23.450 --> 00:23:26.810
In a dash, in a flash, just a
little more now, (Dash! Dash!)

00:23:26.670 --> 00:23:29.550
every step like the wind
neverending (Zoom! Zoom!)

00:23:29.420 --> 00:23:32.470
A twinkling star that we wear
on our sleeves (But only one!)

00:23:32.320 --> 00:23:34.740
Let's let our hearts race
together as one! (Grow up! Shine!)

00:23:34.620 --> 00:23:37.870
One more step, one more push,
just a little more now, (Dash! Dash!)

00:23:37.750 --> 00:23:40.510
each new race like a dream
neverending (Zoom! Zoom!)

00:23:40.400 --> 00:23:43.270
Every one of us will see
our path to the very end!

00:23:43.250 --> 00:23:48.980
Let's run now, everyone!
Let's go! Our starting gate!

